-- Portugal Signs Contracts to Explore for Gold, Other Resources
-- B y   H e n r i q u e   A l m e i d a
-- 2012-07-31T17:10:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-31/portugal-signs-contracts-to-explore-for-gold-other-resources.html
The  Portuguese government  signed
four mining contracts with companies interested in searching for
gold, wolfram and other resources in the southern European
country, Economy Minister Alvaro Santos Pereira said.  Portugal expects the mining industry to remain strong in
coming years and will continue to bet on the sector to stimulate
growth and create jobs in the nation, Santos Pereira said today
in comments broadcast by SIC Noticias television.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henrique Almeida in Lisbon at 
